THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 240 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto the provisions set forth as sections 2, 3 and 4 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. “Affirmation” means a solemn and formal
4 declaration, equivalent in nature to an oath, which asserts that a
5 statement or series of statements is true.
6 Sec. 3. “Oath” means an outward pledge made by a person,
7 signifying that the attestation or promise of the person is given
8 under an immediate sense of responsibility to a higher power or
9 God. The term includes, without limitation, any form of attestation
10 by which a person signifies his or her obligation, under
11 conscience, to perform an act faithfully and truthfully.
12 Sec. 4. 1. Under any circumstance in which an oath or
13 affirmation is required for any purpose:
14 (a) A person may provide either an oath or an affirmation;
15 and
16 (b) An oath and an affirmation have the same legal effect.
17 2. An oath or affirmation may be provided in writing, orally
18 or by any other equivalent mode of communication, including,
19 without limitation, a communication mode, as defined in NRS
20 388.417, in accordance with the circumstances under which the
21 oath or affirmation is required and in compliance with the
22 requirements of any law, regulation or rule of procedure
23 applicable to such circumstances.
24 3. A notarial officer may administer an oath or affirmation in
25 accordance with the requirements of this chapter and in
26 compliance with the requirements of any law, regulation or rule of
27 procedure applicable to the circumstances under which the oath
28 or affirmation is administered, including, without limitation, for:
29 (a) Testimony in a legal proceeding, including, without
30 limitation, a pretrial hearing, examination, deposition or other
31 proceeding; or
32 (b) The assumption of an office or any duties associated with a
33 position that mandates such a pledge.
34 Sec. 5. NRS 240.001 is hereby amended to read as follows:
35 240.001 As used in NRS 240.001 to 240.206, inclusive, and
36 sections 2, 3 and 4 of this act, unless the context otherwise requires,
37 the words and terms defined in NRS 240.002 to 240.0067, inclusive,
38 and sections 2 and 3 of this act have the meanings ascribed to them
39 in those sections.
